Preconditions:
The input list `nums` should not be null.
The input list `nums` should not be empty.
The input list `nums` should only contain non-negative integers.
The input integer `k` should be greater than or equal to zero.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value.
The returned value should be the maximum possible score after applying at most `k` operations.
The returned value should be modulo `10^9 + 7`.